# BEARWATCH — Operations Manifest

**Owner:** BEAR-WATCH chat (any Claude session in this scope)
**Last updated:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Rule:** This file is the source of truth for what is running, how it is kept alive, and what to do when something dies. For scope ownership rules (what BEAR-WATCH owns vs hands off), defer to `_context/CLAUDE.md` "Scope = domain of work" — that's the install-wide authoritative version.

---

## 1. Process Inventory

### 🟢 ALWAYS-ON — Auto-restarted by pm2

| Process | pm2 name | Entry point | Port |
|---------|----------|-------------|------|
| Bot server (dashboard + live bot) | `bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>` | `bear-watch/code/src/server/index.ts` | `<port>` |
| Log rotation (pm2 module) | `pm2-logrotate` | (pm2 module) | n/a |

**How to check:** `pm2 list`
**Restart manually:** `pm2 restart bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>`
**View logs:** `pm2 logs bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>`
**Dashboard:** `http://localhost:<port>/dashboard`

### 🗓️ SCHEDULED — Windows Task Scheduler (or cron on macOS/Linux)

| Task name | Script | Schedule |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| `<INSTALL>-HealthCheck` | `bear-watch/health-check.py` | Every 5 minutes |
| (add others as registered) | | |

