## 3. APIs & Keys

| Service | Where the key lives | Used by |
|---------|---------------------|---------|
| Helius RPC | `runtime/bots/local.env` as `HELIUS_MAINNET_URL=...` | bot server |
| PurpleAir | `runtime/bots/local.env` as `PURPLEAIR_API_KEY=...` | weather-pull.py |
| (add others) | | |

**Hard rule — keys never in committed text.** All keys live in `runtime/bots/local.env` (gitignored) or in external files outside the repo. This MANIFEST documents WHICH env var each service reads from — never the literal key value.

---

## 4. Startup Sequence (after reboot)

Document your install's startup procedure here. Common cases:

- Windows + pm2 doesn't auto-resurrect → manual `pm2 start <config> && pm2 save` from a real PowerShell
- macOS/Linux with systemd → auto-resurrect via systemd unit
- Cloud VPS → systemd or supervisor

---

## 5. Health Check Checklist

```bash
# 1. Bot server
pm2 list

# 2. Server health
curl http://localhost:<port>/health

# 3. Scheduled tasks
Get-ScheduledTask -TaskName "<INSTALL>-*" | Get-ScheduledTaskInfo

# (add install-specific checks)
```

---

## 6. Recovery Procedures

### bear-watch-server-<install-suffix> crashed and didn't auto-restart
```bash
pm2 resurrect
# or
pm2 start <config>
```

### After machine reboot — pm2 not running
*(document the steps for your platform)*

### Disk corruption / state file lost
*(document restore procedure from backups)*

